ef="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=347.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=347.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top bgcolor=#33333 class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=#33333 class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uluciennechantodea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lucienne Chantodea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/3/01 5:32:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=347.topic>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.azathoth.com/misc/EQ/LucBust.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 6 level hard cap on spell damage?</span><hr size=1> Just on a whim I decided to accompany my higher level guildmates on a venture to Skyfire (I'm 38th level). I figured that I would get zero exp and be absolutely worthless. I wasn't, completely <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    I was able to land my ice based dd's on everything we pulled (with the exception of one mature wyvern, who resisted everything a 53 necro threw at it as well) and most often hit for full damage. Got tons of exp to boot <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
My question is this: Was it just me, or has the 6 level hard cap on spell damage been modified? Everything was redredred to me (lots yellow and red to a lvl44 friend there with me). Has anyone else noticed this, or am I making a mistake? It should also be noted that for most of the evening the only cold / fire debuffs thrown on these nasties was my temperate flux effect.<br>
<br>
Just thought I would share this with you more wizened folk to see if I am indeed missing something.<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
Lucienne Chantodea, Norrathian Knights (Innoruuk)<br>
<br>
p.s. Killed my first Wurm! yay! (big day for me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uluciennechantodea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lucienne Chantodea</A> at: 5/3/01 6:41:09 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uveladorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veladorn</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/3/01 7:50:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=347.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://yourpage.blazenet.net/anabelle/triad/valasclose2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 6 level hard cap on spell damage?</span><hr size=1> You are a wizard, the 6 level cap does not apply to wizards over level 35.  There is a level cap, but its greater then 6, its more like 7 or 8.<br>
<br>
This was done in an effort to balance us a year or so ago.<br>
<br>
 <p>Valas Defai<BR>
<a href=http://pub8.ezboard.com/btriadcontinuum><b>Triad Continuum</b></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usilvius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silvius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/3/01 10:07:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=347.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 6 level hard cap on spell damage?</span><hr size=1> Wow I didn't know that, we lose the lvl cap after 35? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uluciennechantodea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lucienne Chantodea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/3/01 10:39:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=347.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.azathoth.com/misc/EQ/LucBust.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 6 level hard cap on spell damage?</span><hr size=1> /boggle<br>
<br>
wow! thanks for the info <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uqaman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qaman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/3/01 12:49:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=347.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 6 level hard cap on spell damage?</span><hr size=1> The level cap *does* apply to Wizards. It is the greater of 6 or 1.2 times your level (at 35 it would be 7 etc). What it doesn't apply to are Lure type spells. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uz0mbie14.showPublicProfile?language=EN>z0mbie14</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/5/01 3:07:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=347.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 6 level hard cap on spell damage?</span><hr size=1> now that is good to know..i shot from 30 to 40 in 2 weeks in OT so i guess i never realized that..thanks for info..a lot <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www,kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/5/01 4:00:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=347.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grimtoo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 6 level hard cap on spell damage?</span><hr size=1> Actually they put in the spell resistance cap to stop their fears of rampaging all wizard groups from flattening things 10 levels over their head.  The fact that this is rediculous and is counterproductive (there is an absolute cap to the amount of xps you can get from any one kill) seems to have eluded Verant.<br>
<br>
But its always been like this: 6+ or 1.2 times your level whichever is higher.  At level 50 you can hit level 60 monsters with normal spells.  And like they say, lures have no level cap at all, they hit anything.  I landed Enticement of Flame on Xenowhatsis in the Lake of Ill Omen (well over level 60) at level 48. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www,kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg BORDER=0> at: 5/6/01 7:34:38 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uveladorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veladorn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/6/01 10:25:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=347.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://yourpage.blazenet.net/anabelle/triad/valasclose2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 6 level hard cap on spell damage?</span><hr size=1> No, was not alawys this way.<br>
<br>
Yes, originally they were afraid wizards would be soloing deep reds for exp so they put in the level camp. (*boggle* wizards can solo blues, thats it, not even even con or yellow, but thats another thread)<br>
<br>
Over time, they gave wizards the ability to hit 1.2 above level as a form of balance since others could use pets, etc.<br>
<br>
So wizard can hit 1.2 above but mages, enchanters and necros are stuck with the 6 above limite.<br>
<br>
 <p>Valas Defai<BR>
<a href=http://pub8.ezboard.com/btriadcontinuum><b>Triad Continuum</b></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvulpdiscoinferno.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vulp DiscoInferno</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.utopiacity.com/whitemage/savepoint.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/6/01 8:18:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=347.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/edit/raw/rawimage/38/1397138.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 6 level hard cap on spell damage?</span><hr size=1> Many skyfire mobs are only in the low 40s <p>____________________________________________________________

